			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here are some very modest proposals of mine.  I apologize if this post gets too long, but I've had a lot of these ideas and I think it would be  efficient to just put them all in one big post and avoid spamming.
<br />

<br />
1.  I propose that there be a 24 hour time limit for retiring.  Personally, I feel that having a 24 hour time limit to destroy a planet (I guess for people to evacuate it or whatnot), but NOT having a 24 hour limit for retiring is a bit senseless.  Staying within Role-Playing context, when an emperor decides to retire from all of his people, shouldnt there at least be a day for all of the information to be relayed and for all of his people to comply or something?
<br />

<br />
2.  An armada grouping page in the War tab.  By this I mean something that you can use to build multiple armadas, like an attack or defense armada, and simply being able to click "Siege Armada" or "Break Blockade Armada" (you'd get to name them whatever you want) instead of having to create a new formation EVERY SINGLE TIME you ATTACK!  Then after a battle, for every fleet you lose, a blank space will appear in that slot of the armada page.  
<br />

<br />
3.  Being able to rename fleets.  I just think it's a peeve later on, when, say, you lose most of your ships in your HBH Doom fleet, and you only have DB dooms to replace them.  Then that fleet is still called HBH Doom fleet.  So how about being able to change it to DB Doom fleet to avoid confusion and simplify things a bit.
<br />

<br />
4.  A bit of an anti-fluffing policy.  Now I KNOW this debate has been going on for quite some time, but I woudl like to present a more modest idea.  It's unfair that a noob with 50k power can be defended with full doom fleets from a player with 3million power.  Perhaps some sort of power barrier for sending allied fleets?  I mean, 600k sounds pretty reasonable to me, because with that difference the higher player is bound to at least lose 2 dooms from a possible full armada, ya know?
<br />

<br />
5.  This one's going to be controversial I know.  I propose making research more difficult/longer.  As it stands now, research is just a minor impediment to players early on.  Most players finish researching within the first week, and then there's another 6 months of the set that's just based around doomstars and the top weapons.  If research would last all throughout the set (yes THAT difficult), then players who decide to follow the HBH path would have that benefit going for them for longer than like 2 days when everyone else gets HBH.  That way, people would have to strategize with the less potent devices and weapons.  It would stretch our minds more.  And having to use lower level ships, like Cruisers and destroyers, to make powerful strategies and such would simply make the game more interesting.  I can't say more fun, because it's never been done, but it'd certainly be an intriguing spectacle to experience.  I mean honestly, doesn't ANYONE else get bored later in the set when it's all about dooms and level 5 weapons?
<br />

<br />
6.  Court ranks seem verily useless to me.  I think they should have a far greater effect.  A duke should be more feared than a baron, and a baron should have more of a say than any non-ranked player.  Thus far it seems that the only worthwhile thing a rank does is change your home planet's name.  I propose that the higher your court rank, the greater your say in the Empire is as far as boons and mediation go.  An idea:
<br />

<br />
No-Rank player:  Can request boon with low chance of getting it.
<br />
Baron:  Higher chance of getting boon
<br />
Viscount: can give any desired name to a second planet of choice, higher boon chance, etc.
<br />
Earl:  something in between all of these and a third named planet
<br />
Marquis:  Has a say in type of boon and a greater chance of getting his desired boon....4th named planet
<br />
Duke:  Has a say in type of boon AND what's in the package.  The better his choice, the less chance he'll get it.  For example, he can say "I want a 10-ship doom fleet MK 4," but has a lower chance of getting this than, say, MK 1 10-ship doom fleet....AND let's not forget a 5th named planet.
<br />

<br />
(this is just a VEEEERRRRRRY rough idea....lots of modifications are needed)
<br />

<br />
Granted, if this were implicated, court ranks would have to be a lot harder to achieve.  Like you'd have to do favors for the Empire like invade a certain target or send them some commanders instead of just bribing up to perfect subject and waiting.  And based on the tasks you perform, you could gain a different type of rank (Knight, Scribe, etc.)
<br />

<br />
7.  Military CM control.  The Mil CM is so out of control and it can get very annoying.  Say you want to make lots of money for investments, so you decide to switch to industry.  Well what if your military CM is 10 on industry!?  That defeats the whole purpose of INDUSTRY mode.  It's called that for a reason...so I propose that players be allowed to influence their military CM or a limit be placed on the max possible Military CM per concentration mode.  For example...10+ on military, 8 on balanced, 6 on industry, etc.  Or, as the first idea goes, being able to fluctuate it maybe once per day within a certain range for each concentration mode.
<br />

<br />
Example:
<br />

<br />
Industry Mode (I'll stick with this ongoing one).  Your industry CM is 10 on this mode, and your military can be anywhere from 5-7 here, and once per day u can change which one it's on.  
<br />

<br />
Now I know the problem of "well what about the gap between starting racial modifiers, like Bossie vs. Agerus," well I'll try to work that out later after people see and give feedback on this idea.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Goodness this is a long ass post.  And I still have many more ideas....if anyone actually responds to each of these ideas I will be SO astonished.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://i132.photobucket.com/albums/q13/LMA11/strecthyleet.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
&lt;Wraith&gt; trout has a cooldown
<br />
&lt;MM&gt; cooldown my ass =p
<br />
* hxc cools down MM's ass.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
