<br />
1.  What do you mean retire with your planets?  
<br />
2.  ...
<br />
3.  This will make you lose all of your fleet's experience.  That's like 3 whole training missions to regain, and when you're at war and want to rename a fleet quickly for easier placement in battle, you want to retain all fleet exp.
<br />
4.  Yes I screwed up here.  Forget the anti-fluffing part...and forget this whole idea as a whole.  I didn't realize that Kenshin started a thread based on modifying this earlier in the set.
<br />
5.  I think jvdthwip has the best points here.  More people might use the research bonus races, and research planets wouldn't become trash later in the set.  And the point of this idea is so that a new player can't just jump in an be 1337 right away.  My goal here was to eliminate all the newbies who jump into megacouncils early on, get uber protected (by council members)  and rape all the planets they want, then easily research all the way to the top and voila, they're better than half the people who started when the set began.
<br />

<br />
6.  Gah...honorary titles..that just makes it seem so useless.  I think "bason" should just be an honorary title (hence the weak power suggestions for the baron), but once you start moving past that, which might actually take some effort, you should get some sort of bonuses.  Plus, wouldn't anyone who requests boons prefer to NOT be sent FLUFF by the Empire?  SO being a duke and having a say in the type of ship u get isn't an entirely horrid idea.
<br />

<br />
7.  Example.  You're in a council that has taken all the projects that give military bonuses and you're an agerus.  So on INDUSTRY your military exceeds ten, making it useless, and severely crippling your net income per turn.  I basically am proposing that players should have the ability to be able to modify their military CM.  Read the idea over again more slowly and picture its points as if they were on the AS screen, and become one with the AS screen, deeply meditating on what I am trying to say, and you might understand it.
<br />

<br />

