				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't know how projects work... Are some projects gained by means of researching technology?
<br />

<br />
If not, theres a way to increase research time... Make some projects that can be only achieved/unlocked by reserching their complementry techs. Also, some techs that have 2 effects or more can be split up?
<br />

<br />
Maybe certain technologies can also be unlocked later in the set, like... You can only reasearch 20 of the 115 techs. After 1 week of playing, the next 20 are unlocked. The next week, 20 more. The numbers can be changed, of course, to a more pleasing system, but the gist is: Perhaps there can be a time-progressive tech tree that allows techs only to be researched after a certain amt of time.
<br />

<br />
In this system it would take 5 weeks for a new player to gain all techs, and again Research-happy races will be valuable and Lab-ridden planets won't be useless.
<br />

<br />
Through experience, I've found that it takes almost no time to research all techs... It's almost as if you may as well get rid of the entire feature and give them to me, the entire system is flawed... Revisions to Research need to be made.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">Gamer through and through</span>
