			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1. No, this isn't really an issue.  This has been debated before but for the sake of argument I'll repeat it again here.
<br />

<br />
Long Story Short, they are hurt as much or more than you especially if Idea 5 is implemented.  Its kind of a kamakazee move on their part.  9 times out of 10 you'll be back to 100% way before they are back to 50%.  The key to recovering from this is the same as recovering from any near death situation in this game.  Teamwork.  I don't think its anymore devastating than losing in any other war, you just have to get your planets back from somebody else.  No big deal there are plenty of players out there.
<br />

<br />
2. This Idea was implemented at one time in the original version of archspace back when half the races were unusable and such.  This Code likely still exists in the Devs hands somewhere, I too want it to make a comeback, but it probably won't for quite some time.  The reason for this is because of the reason it was removed in the first place, it caused way too many bugs to validate it as it simply made things easier and wasn't vital. I think if it were done again it would have to be made from scratch.  In the end I think it may be done at some point after everything else has been taken care of, but don't hold your breath for any time soon.  But hey if its that important to you find somebody to code it for the devs i'm sure they'll be willing to give it a trial run on the dev server.
<br />

<br />
3. I too wish they would implement this, I couldn't imagine that it would be very difficult.  I also wish you could rename planets but thats just because it would be interesting if you could name them when you get them from expeditions and if somebody steals them they are stuck with that name.  But I'm sure that would get crazy fast.  But in the end I know they have heard this one before and will probably be done at some point but it likely gettng a low priority for the other more pressing issues, but i'm sure your aware of that.
<br />

<br />
4. I totally agree with this policy but I do see plenty of exploits come from this.  Not to mention a large rise in fluffing, but as we all know with fluffing comes vulerabilities.  I simply see this as being a small roadblock for the people your trying to stop with this.  The vets won't be hindered much by this.  However I'd rather hinder them a little than none at all.
<br />

<br />
5.  Now I really like this Idea, again an old Idea but I have always liked it.  I personally think it should take so long that you arn't finishing until the very end of the set and maybe only 30 or so players may have actually finished.  I know what you mean about getting bored.  Its like in football, how many people leave when the other team is up by thirty?  A tight game is just more fun.  I think this would be awesome, and I would also like to see more techs implemented and different weapon paths so that for example you have a different tech tree for HBH than you do for DB that way you won't likely have both DB and HBH at the end of the set.  That forces you to work as a council better, you'll have players that take the HBH tree and others that take the DB tree, and you work together to put a complete armada out.    Now thats just an example as all of this will likely have to be balanced out.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Note:  For the above poster who mentioned late arivals to the game, I agree with you that those who start late will be at a disadvantage.  However, if you take the current system and bring it to effect in this system it won't be so harsh.  See after about a week the techs research faster, and after about two weeks even faster.  This allows those who are behind to catch up, but beyond that if they enter the game within the first few weeks they will still stand a fighting chance.  Its not like now where you start late, and in your first fight its your lasers and nukes vs. his Anti-Matter missiles or whatever.  He might only have plasma because its going so much slower.  The point is its not beyond reach.  If your starting a month- a month and a half late, even under the current system barring some powerful allies you stand little to no chance of catching up, to the other guys with maxed out techs and 50+ planets in the remainding time in the set.
<br />

<br />
6.  This just seems pointless to me, its not necessary and won't impact the game much.  You already have an increased chance of boon with the higher ranks.  I don't see much point for this other than to simply have a special name mostly for bragging rights.  Its just kind nifty to have.  I like the Idea of the names, but its always been pointless, always will be pointless, and always should be pointless.
<br />

<br />
7.  Well I think it is kinda dumb that this can happen I just think that what needs to be done is somthing different.  I think that the only reason that you can do that is because of projects and race. I think it should be harder to obtain projects like say you can only buy 1 project a week or somthing, I know thats drastic but if you combine that with Idea 5 then your set for a much slower paced game with more dogfighting and less david vs. god scenario.  Lower the rate at which you get techs, lower the rate at which you get projects, and whats the first thing your going to do?  Your going to very carefully select which projects and techs you take, because you know you can't have them all.  Its kinda like in WoW you see all these cool powers but you know you can't have them all so you select which ones you want the most.  It just makes the game more fun.  And gives each charachter a more unique feel.  You can say your one of the only bosallians who don't use psychic weapons or somthing.  To me thats a lot more fun than having everything because if you have everything then everybody does.  I like to know that I have somthing that some or most others don't have.  It just makes it that much more interesting.
<br />

<br />
1. No
<br />
2. Yes, but don't hold your breath.
<br />
3. Yes, but not for a while
<br />
4. Yes, but not going to acomplish much
<br />
5. Yes, but lets take it a few steps further
<br />
6. No
<br />
7. Yes, but lets do it differently<br />_________________<br />"Those who are skilled in combat do not become angered, those who are skilled at winning do not become afraid.  Thus the wise win before they fight while the ignorant fight to win."  --Zhuge Liang
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.junk.ws/halo2/sig/Midnight%2039/sig7.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://eog.myfastforum.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Echoes of Genocide</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
